1232
00:36:32,920 --> 00:36:33,320
Okay.

1233
00:36:33,320 --> 00:36:33,800
One moment.

1234
00:36:33,800 --> 00:36:34,360
Guests?

1235
00:36:34,360 --> 00:36:35,280
Isn't this our house?

1236
00:36:35,280 --> 00:36:36,240
Why are we guests now?

1237
00:36:36,240 --> 00:36:37,780
(Why are the An family now guests?)

1238
00:36:37,960 --> 00:36:39,560
The current date

1239
00:36:39,560 --> 00:36:40,960
is March 25,

1240
00:36:40,960 --> 00:36:42,960
is 1996.

1241
00:36:43,700 --> 00:36:45,500
(1996)

1242
00:36:45,760 --> 00:36:46,200
What?

1243
00:36:55,360 --> 00:36:57,120
The current date is...

1244
00:36:58,120 --> 00:36:59,320
1996.

1245
00:37:32,840 --> 00:37:34,240
(An Glass Factory)
Guys, we time-traveled.

1246
00:37:34,580 --> 00:37:35,840
(Why did they return to 1996?)

1247
00:37:35,840 --> 00:37:37,520
1996 means

1248
00:37:37,520 --> 00:37:38,960
(Wedding)
the year An San died.

1249
00:37:40,160 --> 00:37:41,560
What's today's date?

1250
00:37:41,560 --> 00:37:43,960
Today is March 25.

1251
00:37:44,640 --> 00:37:46,040
(Family curse victim: An San)

1252
00:37:46,040 --> 00:37:47,200
on March 25.

1253
00:37:48,160 --> 00:37:49,280
The day An San died.

1254
00:37:50,500 --> 00:37:55,900
(Back to the day An San died)

1255
00:37:55,920 --> 00:37:59,760
Here's the thing.

1256
00:37:59,760 --> 00:38:01,520
needs a rehearsal soon.

1257
00:38:01,520 --> 00:38:02,360
Bride An San

1258
00:38:02,360 --> 00:38:03,880
is ready.

1259
00:38:03,880 --> 00:38:04,840
An San?

1260
00:38:04,840 --> 00:38:05,760
(An San is the bride)

1261
00:38:05,760 --> 00:38:07,080
An San?

1262
00:38:08,680 --> 00:38:09,960
Have you seen her today?

1263
00:38:09,960 --> 00:38:11,960
I heard she arrived,

1264
00:38:11,960 --> 00:38:13,080
but I haven't seen her in person.

1265
00:38:14,600 --> 00:38:16,080
We've got a problem.

1266
00:38:16,080 --> 00:38:17,200
We need everyone's help.

1267
00:38:18,400 --> 00:38:20,040
The groom had an emergency.

1268
00:38:20,040 --> 00:38:21,400
So we need to back up!

1269
00:38:21,400 --> 00:38:21,960
No way.

1270
00:38:26,080 --> 00:38:26,800
You guessed it.

1271
00:38:27,160 --> 00:38:28,280
Seriously?

1272
00:38:29,320 --> 00:38:30,840
But what about Xi Hu?

1273
00:38:30,980 --> 00:38:31,880
(Xi Hu, let me explain)

1274
00:38:31,880 --> 00:38:33,160
That's fine. Just standing in

1275
00:38:33,160 --> 00:38:34,800
for the rehearsal.

1276
00:38:35,200 --> 00:38:36,840
Who's standing in?

1277
00:38:36,840 --> 00:38:38,680
I have four brothers here.

1278
00:38:38,680 --> 00:38:39,800
Take your pick.

1279
00:38:42,060 --> 00:38:42,540
(Side Quest)

1280
00:38:42,540 --> 00:38:42,980
(Side Quest triggered)

1281
00:38:42,980 --> 00:38:43,740
(Help the Butler complete
the wedding rehearsal)

1282
00:38:43,740 --> 00:38:44,780
(Choose a stand-in groom for An San)

1283
00:38:46,000 --> 00:38:46,760
My pick?

1284
00:38:46,760 --> 00:38:47,600
My opinion doesn't matter.

1285
00:38:47,600 --> 00:38:48,920
(Almost got picked)
Volunteers only.

1286
00:38:48,920 --> 00:38:49,640
Okay?

1287
00:38:49,640 --> 00:38:51,160
Any takers?

1288
00:38:51,160 --> 00:38:52,820
I'm married.

1289
00:38:52,820 --> 00:38:53,520
(Upholding his morals)

1290
00:38:53,520 --> 00:38:55,200
(All taken men here)
Me too.

1291
00:38:55,200 --> 00:38:55,720
Stand in!

1292
00:38:55,720 --> 00:38:56,960
You're not actually getting married.

1293
00:38:56,960 --> 00:38:58,760
Youngest goes.

1294
00:38:58,760 --> 00:39:00,500
(Thanks, but married)
The youngest can't either.

1295
00:39:01,600 --> 00:39:02,320
Got it.

1296
00:39:02,320 --> 00:39:03,720
All four of you, gather up.

1297
00:39:03,720 --> 00:39:05,400
We'll leave it to fate.

1298
00:39:05,640 --> 00:39:05,960
Fine.

1299
00:39:05,960 --> 00:39:06,240
Alright.

1300
00:39:06,240 --> 00:39:07,000
(Fair and square)
Okay then.

1301
00:39:07,000 --> 00:39:07,480
Whatever happens, happens.

1302
00:39:07,480 --> 00:39:09,560
This is called destiny.

1303
00:39:10,280 --> 00:39:11,680
Destiny. Let's go.

1304
00:39:12,320 --> 00:39:13,920
Rock paper scissors.

1305
00:39:13,920 --> 00:39:15,280
Winner goes.

1306
00:39:15,600 --> 00:39:16,560
Okay.

1307
00:39:16,560 --> 00:39:16,960
Okay. Let's go.

1308
00:39:16,960 --> 00:39:18,440
Rock paper scissors!

1309
00:39:18,940 --> 00:39:19,720
(Fist vs paper)

1310
00:39:19,720 --> 00:39:20,160
You lost.

1311
00:39:20,160 --> 00:39:20,760
You're out.

1312
00:39:20,760 --> 00:39:21,680
You three keep going.

1313
00:39:21,960 --> 00:39:22,560
What?

1314
00:39:22,560 --> 00:39:23,280
(Eliminated from groom contention)

1315
00:39:23,280 --> 00:39:24,080
Rock paper scissors!

1316
00:39:24,100 --> 00:39:25,380
(Fist vs paper)

1317
00:39:25,980 --> 00:39:26,380
(Wait, that's wrong)

1318
00:39:26,380 --> 00:39:26,960
(Hold on)
You go!

1319
00:39:27,640 --> 00:39:27,960
I won!

1320
00:39:27,960 --> 00:39:29,000
(What exactly are they celebrating)

1321
00:39:29,000 --> 00:39:29,960
You go!

1322
00:39:29,960 --> 00:39:30,840
Congratulations!

1323
00:39:31,400 --> 00:39:33,640
Congratulations!

1324
00:39:34,360 --> 00:39:36,880
This is destiny.

1325
00:39:38,360 --> 00:39:39,120
Honey...

1326
00:39:39,640 --> 00:39:40,960
(I can explain)
This isn't what I want.

1327
00:39:40,960 --> 00:39:41,960
It's a fake wedding.

1328
00:39:41,960 --> 00:39:43,120
Your wife is back in 2016.

1329
00:39:44,440 --> 00:39:44,720
Hold on.

1330
00:39:44,720 --> 00:39:45,880
I need to confirm something.

1331
00:39:45,880 --> 00:39:46,800
Go ahead.

1332
00:39:50,760 --> 00:39:52,600
Does the groom have
to go anywhere alone?

1333
00:39:52,600 --> 00:39:53,040
No.

1334
00:39:53,040 --> 00:39:54,420
(The only thing he cared about)
Okay.

1335
00:39:59,480 --> 00:40:00,840
Okay.

1336
00:40:00,840 --> 00:40:02,000
Everything stays right here.

1337
00:40:02,000 --> 00:40:02,860
Good. Right here.

1338
00:40:02,860 --> 00:40:03,560
(Now I can relax)

1339
00:40:03,560 --> 00:40:05,380
(Just kidding)
The bride might be a ghost though.

1340
00:40:05,920 --> 00:40:07,040
(You're terrible)
A ghost bride?

1341
00:40:07,040 --> 00:40:08,240
She'll be wearing a veil.

1342
00:40:08,500 --> 00:40:09,320
(So mean)

1343
00:40:09,320 --> 00:40:10,000
It's a happy occasion!

1344
00:40:10,000 --> 00:40:11,200
There's nothing like that.

1345
00:40:11,200 --> 00:40:11,640
Right?

1346
00:40:11,820 --> 00:40:13,360
(You're the one stirring things up)

1347
00:40:13,360 --> 00:40:14,920
And the rest of you

1348
00:40:14,920 --> 00:40:16,600
will be our groomsmen and bridesmaids.

1349
00:40:16,600 --> 00:40:17,000
No problem.

1350
00:40:17,000 --> 00:40:18,160
Hold on.

1351
00:40:18,160 --> 00:40:18,880
One, two, three, four...

1352
00:40:19,480 --> 00:40:20,160
There's a problem.

1353
00:40:20,160 --> 00:40:20,680
Looks like

1354
00:40:20,680 --> 00:40:21,920
the groomsmen and bridesmaids

1355
00:40:21,920 --> 00:40:23,200
