1402
00:41:20,540 --> 00:41:22,020
(Looks like that one's yours)

1403
00:41:22,120 --> 00:41:22,720
What?

1404
00:41:24,200 --> 00:41:25,720
(It's got your name on it)
That purple one is definitely yours.

1405
00:41:25,720 --> 00:41:26,940
(Are you serious)

1406
00:41:27,220 --> 00:41:28,780
(Vintage sequin purple gown)

1407
00:41:30,880 --> 00:41:32,280
The purple is gorgeous. I want it.

1408
00:41:32,680 --> 00:41:34,320
(Absolutely stunning)
It'll really complement your skin tone.

1409
00:41:34,320 --> 00:41:35,480
Destiny.

1410
00:41:35,480 --> 00:41:36,760
My "Purple Butt" got this!

1411
00:41:36,760 --> 00:41:37,480
(Own it)
"Purple Butt."

1412
00:41:37,480 --> 00:41:38,360
"Purple Butt" can do it.

1413
00:41:38,360 --> 00:41:39,480
This one's mine.

1414
00:41:39,480 --> 00:41:40,080
Alright, let's go upstairs

1415
00:41:40,080 --> 00:41:41,000
and get changed.

1416
00:41:41,000 --> 00:41:42,680
I'll wait right here for everyone!

1417
00:41:43,920 --> 00:41:46,240
The length is just right!

1418
00:41:46,240 --> 00:41:48,280
It was destiny that I'd wear this.

1419
00:41:48,280 --> 00:41:49,600
Which room do we change in?

1420
00:41:49,600 --> 00:41:50,400
Left side.

1421
00:41:50,400 --> 00:41:51,080
(Bridal suite, do not enter)

1422
00:41:51,080 --> 00:41:51,520
This way, right?

1423
00:41:51,520 --> 00:41:51,880
Yes.

1424
00:41:52,440 --> 00:41:54,440
(Excited)
I can't wait!

1425
00:41:54,440 --> 00:41:55,660
(Transformation in progress)

1426
00:41:57,220 --> 00:41:57,720
(Rest and Recharge)

1427
00:41:57,720 --> 00:41:58,420
(Resting resets battle fatigue.
Recharging restores energy.)

1428
00:41:58,420 --> 00:41:58,860
(If you want to go far in this dungeon,)

1429
00:41:58,880 --> 00:41:59,500
(treat rest and recharge
as passive skills.)

1430
00:42:29,520 --> 00:42:30,840
Let's go, Purple.

1431
00:42:30,840 --> 00:42:32,720
This looks incredible.

1432
00:42:32,720 --> 00:42:34,200
Almost too good.

1433
00:42:34,200 --> 00:42:35,360
Come on, everyone. Let's move.

1434
00:42:36,080 --> 00:42:36,560
Let's go.

1435
00:42:38,340 --> 00:42:39,500
(Shy groom)

1436
00:42:39,740 --> 00:42:41,380
(Dominant bridesmaid)

1437
00:42:41,900 --> 00:42:45,580
(Cool-as-ice groomsman)

1438
00:42:48,620 --> 00:42:49,980
(Confident)

1439
00:42:52,280 --> 00:42:53,280
What are you laughing at?

1440
00:42:53,280 --> 00:42:53,920
Not bad, right?

1441
00:42:53,920 --> 00:42:54,440
Not bad.

1442
00:42:54,440 --> 00:42:54,960
Why are you...

1443
00:42:54,960 --> 00:42:55,740
(Sudden self-doubt, but make it cute)

1444
00:42:55,880 --> 00:42:56,800
Thank you.

1445
00:42:56,800 --> 00:42:57,760
(Other groomsman in position)
Groomsmen, bridesmaids,

1446
00:42:57,760 --> 00:42:58,640
over here please.

1447
00:43:01,280 --> 00:43:01,880
Why didn't

1448
00:43:01,880 --> 00:43:03,720
you two greet me when you saw me?

1449
00:43:07,380 --> 00:43:09,060
(An Er, 20-years-younger edition)

1450
00:43:09,820 --> 00:43:10,940
(Wait, isn't that a familiar face?)

1451
00:43:11,000 --> 00:43:11,840
You look so worn out!

1452
00:43:11,840 --> 00:43:12,820
(One day apart feels like twenty years)

1453
00:43:13,800 --> 00:43:14,840
Uncle.

1454
00:43:14,840 --> 00:43:15,480
Uncle Er.

1455
00:43:16,240 --> 00:43:17,560
Er!

1456
00:43:18,200 --> 00:43:18,880
Brother!

1457
00:43:19,280 --> 00:43:20,040
Uncle Er.

1458
00:43:20,040 --> 00:43:21,520
Brother!

1459
00:43:21,800 --> 00:43:22,720
How does he know us?

1460
00:43:24,240 --> 00:43:24,720
Wait.

1461
00:43:24,720 --> 00:43:26,040
How old were we in 1996?

1462
00:43:26,040 --> 00:43:26,840
Mid-twenties.

1463
00:43:26,840 --> 00:43:27,620
(24 years old, 3 years old)

1464
00:43:27,960 --> 00:43:28,880
In 1996, we were

1465
00:43:29,520 --> 00:43:29,880
five.

1466
00:43:29,880 --> 00:43:30,580
(5 years old)

1467
00:43:30,800 --> 00:43:31,640
You two don't recognize him?

1468
00:43:31,640 --> 00:43:32,760
(Too young back then)
You two weren't...

1469
00:43:32,960 --> 00:43:33,840
Mr. Wu, hurry up!

1470
00:43:33,840 --> 00:43:35,120
Where are the flower children?

1471
00:43:35,120 --> 00:43:36,680
(Another familiar face)
There's Mr. Wu also.

1472
00:43:37,200 --> 00:43:38,160
Let me see what Mr. Wu

1473
00:43:38,160 --> 00:43:39,480
looked like back in 1996.

1474
00:43:39,480 --> 00:43:40,480
See if it's really him.

1475
00:43:42,440 --> 00:43:43,920
Mr. Wu!

1476
00:43:44,840 --> 00:43:46,360
Coming!

1477
00:43:48,200 --> 00:43:49,720
I've been with this family twenty years.

1478
00:43:49,720 --> 00:43:50,660
(Mr. Wu, first day on the job edition)

1479
00:43:56,680 --> 00:43:57,440
It really is him.

1480
00:43:57,440 --> 00:43:58,840
Isn't that you guys?

1481
00:43:59,640 --> 00:44:01,880
Is that An Xiaowen you're holding?

1482
00:44:04,680 --> 00:44:05,960
An Xiaoding.

1483
00:44:06,600 --> 00:44:08,520
Miss Xiaowen.

1484
00:44:09,040 --> 00:44:09,440
Miss Xiaowen.

1485
00:44:09,440 --> 00:44:10,640
Xiaowen!

1486
00:44:11,800 --> 00:44:13,480
You're so pretty.

1487
00:44:13,480 --> 00:44:15,160
I want to be this pretty when I grow up.

1488
00:44:15,160 --> 00:44:17,240
You want to look like me
when you grow up?

1489
00:44:17,240 --> 00:44:19,960
You'll be even prettier than me.

1490
00:44:19,960 --> 00:44:21,640
Mr. He.

1491
00:44:22,680 --> 00:44:23,520
Hello.

1492
00:44:23,520 --> 00:44:24,720
You're so cool.

1493
00:44:24,720 --> 00:44:25,320
You're cool too.

1494
00:44:25,320 --> 00:44:26,480
I want to be this cool someday!

1495
00:44:27,040 --> 00:44:27,640
You will be.

1496
00:44:27,640 --> 00:44:28,600
Way cooler than me.

1497
00:44:28,600 --> 00:44:31,440
Mr. Ding.

1498
00:44:31,440 --> 00:44:32,560
Is that little Ding?

1499
00:44:33,360 --> 00:44:34,680
Hello, Mr. Ding.

1500
00:44:34,680 --> 00:44:35,720
Hello.

1501
00:44:35,720 --> 00:44:36,640
Look at you as a kid.

1502
00:44:36,640 --> 00:44:37,640
An Xiaoding.

1503
00:44:37,640 --> 00:44:38,880
Do you know who I am?

1504
00:44:38,880 --> 00:44:39,640
Who am I?

1505
00:44:41,120 --> 00:44:42,720
I'm An Xiaoding too.

1506
00:44:42,720 --> 00:44:43,800
Mr. Ding.

1507
00:44:43,800 --> 00:44:45,200
Anything you want to say?

1508
00:44:46,480 --> 00:44:49,040
I want to be as cool
as you when I grow up.

1509
00:44:49,040 --> 00:44:50,280
Can't you just aim to be as cool as me?

1510
00:44:50,280 --> 00:44:51,060
(I'm literally your future self)

1511
00:44:52,600 --> 00:44:54,200
You'll definitely be even cooler.

1512
00:44:54,200 --> 00:44:54,840
Right?

1513
00:44:56,740 --> 00:44:58,020
(Love to hear that)

1514
00:44:58,040 --> 00:44:59,680
Come on, strike a pose.

1515
00:44:59,680 --> 00:45:00,040
Look where?

1516
00:45:00,040 --> 00:45:00,960
Oh, over there.

1517
00:45:00,960 --> 00:45:01,680
This way.

1518
00:45:01,680 --> 00:45:03,580
Perfect.

1519
00:45:05,800 --> 00:45:07,000
Nice.

1520
00:45:08,320 --> 00:45:09,880
Come on, strike a pose.

1521
00:45:15,320 --> 00:45:16,940
(That's my boy)
See that?

1522
00:45:17,960 --> 00:45:19,600
Had it from day one.

1523
00:45:19,760 --> 00:45:21,160
Yeah, looks more like you actually.

1524
00:45:21,160 --> 00:45:22,080
Like me.

1525
00:45:23,520 --> 00:45:25,560
Alright. Counting down from three.

1526
00:45:25,560 --> 00:45:26,960
Our bride is coming.

1527
00:45:26,960 --> 00:45:27,680
Everyone ready?

1528
00:45:27,680 --> 00:45:28,880
Ready.

1529
00:45:28,880 --> 00:45:30,460
(Bridesmaid standby)

1530
00:45:30,580 --> 00:45:32,500
(Groomsmen standby)

1531
00:45:32,900 --> 00:45:34,320
(Groom standby)

1532
00:45:34,320 --> 00:45:35,480
Alright. Here we go.

1533
00:45:35,480 --> 00:45:35,960
Three.

1534
00:45:36,760 --> 00:45:37,360
Two.

1535
00:45:38,840 --> 00:45:39,200
One.

1536
00:45:39,960 --> 00:45:41,680
I've waited so long for this day.

1537
00:45:41,680 --> 00:45:42,640
My bride!

1538
00:45:49,180 --> 00:45:50,180
(An family. An San. An Songqiu.)

1539
00:46:03,360 --> 00:46:04,560
Beautiful!

1540
00:46:19,000 --> 00:46:20,120
Everyone can see

1541
00:46:20,120 --> 00:46:23,440
the founder of An Glass Factory,

1542
00:46:23,440 --> 00:46:25,440
Mr. An

1543
00:46:25,440 --> 00:46:27,680
walking the bride down the aisle.

1544
00:46:27,680 --> 00:46:29,960
Please now place the bride's hand

1545
00:46:29,960 --> 00:46:32,440
into the groom's.

1546
00:46:32,440 --> 00:46:33,860
(Fully in character)

1547
00:46:35,160 --> 00:46:36,440
Groom.

1548
00:46:36,760 --> 00:46:38,600
Congratulations!

1549
00:46:41,880 --> 00:46:43,120
A round of applause for them.

1550
00:46:45,740 --> 00:46:47,140
(My boy's all grown up)

1551
00:46:48,160 --> 00:46:49,080
Congratulations.

1552
00:46:49,640 --> 00:46:51,440
Please, let our founder

1553
00:46:51,440 --> 00:46:52,960
take a seat.

1554
00:46:53,640 --> 00:46:56,120
In this joyful moment,

1555
00:46:56,640 --> 00:46:58,640
(Tearing up)
our groom is moved to tears.

1556
00:46:58,640 --> 00:47:01,200
Overwhelmed with joy.

1557
00:47:03,880 --> 00:47:04,720
♪Waited so long♪

1558
00:47:04,720 --> 00:47:06,880
(The moment moved him to song)
♪Finally here today♪

1559
00:47:08,580 --> 00:47:09,940
(Way too into it)

1560
00:47:10,120 --> 00:47:10,760
Groom,

1561
00:47:11,200 --> 00:47:12,640
seeing your bride today,

1562
00:47:12,640 --> 00:47:13,880
any thoughts?

1563
00:47:20,440 --> 00:47:21,200
Never dared imagine.

1564
00:47:24,080 --> 00:47:26,360
Never dared imagine

1565
00:47:26,360 --> 00:47:28,560
(A road he never envisioned)
seeing this someday.

1566
00:47:28,560 --> 00:47:30,040
Doesn't matter if you dared.

1567
00:47:30,040 --> 00:47:30,920
It's not actually you anyway.

1568
00:47:30,920 --> 00:47:31,700
(Just run through the motions)

1569
00:47:31,760 --> 00:47:32,280
You're overthinking it.

1570
00:47:32,280 --> 00:47:32,640
Way overthinking.

1571
00:47:32,780 --> 00:47:33,980
(All that brain power for nothing)

1572
00:47:35,640 --> 00:47:36,640
Looks like the bride

1573
00:47:36,640 --> 00:47:37,320
has something to say.

1574
00:47:38,920 --> 00:47:42,240
Today is a very important day for me.

1575
00:47:47,280 --> 00:47:49,560
My brothers,

1576
00:47:49,860 --> 00:47:51,080
(Ke)

1577
00:47:51,080 --> 00:47:51,760
sisters-in-law,

1578
00:47:52,280 --> 00:47:53,520
nieces and nephews, all here.

1579
00:47:53,520 --> 00:47:54,760
(sister-in-law, niece, nephew)

1580
00:47:54,760 --> 00:47:56,160
In this moment,

1581
00:47:56,160 --> 00:47:57,720
I'm already so happy.

1582
00:48:02,440 --> 00:48:03,400
Somehow I always knew

1583
00:48:04,400 --> 00:48:06,160
this day was coming.

1584
00:48:08,600 --> 00:48:10,960
And now, with all of you

1585
00:48:10,960 --> 00:48:12,240
as my witness,

1586
00:48:14,000 --> 00:48:15,120
I walk toward my destiny.

1587
00:48:20,640 --> 00:48:21,800
What?

1588
00:48:22,120 --> 00:48:23,160
That sounded

1589
00:48:23,160 --> 00:48:23,920
a little ominous.

1590
00:48:24,100 --> 00:48:26,420
(A sense of dread)

1591
00:48:30,320 --> 00:48:30,880
What's happening?

1592
00:48:38,520 --> 00:48:38,840
She's...

1593
00:48:38,840 --> 00:48:40,880
bleeding from her mouth.

1594
00:48:41,600 --> 00:48:42,520
She's coughing up blood.

1595
00:48:42,520 --> 00:48:43,560
It's okay.

1596
00:48:44,740 --> 00:48:54,340
(Special prop for narrative purposes,
no harmful intent)

1597
00:48:54,360 --> 00:48:55,640
She's dead.

1598
00:48:55,640 --> 00:48:56,840
Is she dead?

1599
00:48:57,940 --> 00:49:00,820
(Everyone witnesses the
second curse unfold)

1600
00:49:00,820 --> 00:49:03,460
(Special prop for narrative purposes,
no harmful intent)

1601
00:49:03,460 --> 00:49:04,060
(This segment contains horror content)

1602
00:49:04,060 --> 00:49:04,840
(Viewer discretion advised for minors)

1603
00:49:04,840 --> 00:49:05,520
Nobody move!

1604
00:49:06,000 --> 00:49:06,720
Nobody move!

1605
00:49:07,200 --> 00:49:08,720
Don't look.

1606
00:49:08,720 --> 00:49:09,480
(Covering her eyes)
I've got you.

1607
00:49:10,000 --> 00:49:11,400
Power's out. It'll come back.

1608
00:49:11,400 --> 00:49:12,520
It's okay.

1609
00:49:12,960 --> 00:49:14,240
Can you protect me too?

1610
00:49:14,240 --> 00:49:14,920
You protect me.

1611
00:49:14,920 --> 00:49:16,100
(Wen is scared too)
We protect each other.

1612
00:49:19,760 --> 00:49:20,920
It's the Puppet!

1613
00:49:23,760 --> 00:49:24,880
It's the Puppet!

1614
00:49:24,880 --> 00:49:25,680
It's here!

1615
00:49:28,340 --> 00:49:30,180
(Comforting)

1616
00:49:30,200 --> 00:49:30,880
When the Puppet appears,

1617
00:49:30,880 --> 00:49:31,760
someone dies.

1618
00:49:31,820 --> 00:49:33,740
(The An family curse has struck)

1619
00:49:34,200 --> 00:49:35,280
I'm going to have nightmares tonight.

1620
00:49:36,800 --> 00:49:37,680
You all saw the Puppet...

1621
00:49:37,680 --> 00:49:38,300
(Lights back on)

1622
00:49:44,700 --> 00:49:46,580
(What is going on)

1623
00:49:46,960 --> 00:49:47,880
You scared me.

1624
00:49:48,600 --> 00:49:49,240
What happened?

1625
00:49:49,240 --> 00:49:50,440
Why did the bridesmaid steal the groom?

1626
00:49:50,440 --> 00:49:51,120
(Bridesmaid steals the groom)
What's going on?

1627
00:49:51,120 --> 00:49:51,800
It's fine.

1628
00:49:51,800 --> 00:49:52,400
Hold on.

1629
00:49:53,600 --> 00:49:54,440
What's happening?

1630
00:49:56,820 --> 00:49:58,020
(Textbook form)

1631
00:49:58,520 --> 00:50:00,600
Groom, why are you holding
the bridesmaid's hand?

1632
00:50:01,500 --> 00:50:04,140
(Textbook form, muscle
memory at this point)

1633
00:50:04,140 --> 00:50:06,260
(Peak Dad mode)

1634
00:50:06,280 --> 00:50:08,200
It's fine.

1635
00:50:08,200 --> 00:50:09,280
(Let's all just forget this)

1636
00:50:09,280 --> 00:50:10,800
Hey, where did the bride go?

1637
00:50:12,620 --> 00:50:14,100
(Bride An San has vanished)

1638
00:50:16,560 --> 00:50:17,200
Where is she?

1639
00:50:23,840 --> 00:50:24,440
Come on, sir.

1640
00:50:27,320 --> 00:50:28,680
Everyone, please listen.

1641
00:50:29,520 --> 00:50:30,760
I didn't expect

1642
00:50:30,760 --> 00:50:32,000
something like this to happen today.

1643
00:50:32,840 --> 00:50:33,560
Who could have known.

1644
00:50:34,960 --> 00:50:35,680
The wedding is cancelled.

1645
00:50:37,800 --> 00:50:38,320
Everyone,

1646
00:50:38,320 --> 00:50:39,560
please leave.

1647
00:50:39,920 --> 00:50:40,440
Why do we have to leave?

1648
00:50:40,440 --> 00:50:41,560
Why?

1649
00:50:41,560 --> 00:50:42,520
Everyone out.

1650
00:50:42,520 --> 00:50:43,120
What's going on?

1651
00:50:43,120 --> 00:50:44,360
The rings haven't even
been exchanged yet.

1652
00:50:46,180 --> 00:50:47,780
(Everyone leaves)

1653
00:50:47,800 --> 00:50:49,120
Why do we have to leave?

1654
00:50:50,820 --> 00:50:52,580
(An Songqiu leaves)

1655
00:50:53,040 --> 00:50:53,720
Don't cancel it.

1656
00:50:53,720 --> 00:50:54,600
(We haven't even eaten yet)

1657
00:50:54,600 --> 00:50:56,640
You were only standing in to begin with.

1658
00:50:56,640 --> 00:50:57,280
Too into it.

1659
00:50:57,340 --> 00:50:58,060
(Fully immersed)

1660
00:50:58,540 --> 00:51:00,020
(Ding really wanted that dinner)

1661
00:51:00,360 --> 00:51:02,000
Alright, we need to get out of here too.

1662
00:51:03,840 --> 00:51:04,760
Wait, don't go yet. What about us?

1663
00:51:04,760 --> 00:51:05,520
Where do we go?

1664
00:51:05,520 --> 00:51:06,200
I didn't expect

1665
00:51:06,200 --> 00:51:07,080
any of this to happen.

1666
00:51:07,680 --> 00:51:08,280
You're not leaving.

1667
00:51:08,280 --> 00:51:09,240
(Got him)
I can't leave?

1668
00:51:09,240 --> 00:51:10,080
You're not leaving.

1669
00:51:10,360 --> 00:51:12,000
Right after the bride collapsed,

1670
00:51:12,000 --> 00:51:12,640
she just vanished.

1671
00:51:12,640 --> 00:51:13,240
I have no idea.

1672
00:51:13,240 --> 00:51:14,800
You're not saying I did it?

1673
00:51:15,200 --> 00:51:15,760
Nothing to do with you.

1674
00:51:15,760 --> 00:51:16,840
Then take this diamond ring

1675
00:51:16,840 --> 00:51:17,560
as an apology.

1676
00:51:17,560 --> 00:51:18,420
(At least nobody leaves empty-handed)

1677
00:51:19,200 --> 00:51:20,000
I can't take that.

1678
00:51:20,000 --> 00:51:20,600
(Has standards)
I really can't.

1679
00:51:20,840 --> 00:51:22,520
You're surprisingly principled.

1680
00:51:22,720 --> 00:51:24,560
The wontons in Chongqing
are amazing though.

1681
00:51:24,560 --> 00:51:24,960
Really?

1682
00:51:24,960 --> 00:51:26,400
(Genuinely hungry)
I'll have to try them sometime.

1683
00:51:26,680 --> 00:51:28,040
When these kids grow up

1684
00:51:28,040 --> 00:51:29,360
and get married, they'll
all come find you.

1685
00:51:30,080 --> 00:51:31,160
Deal. You all come find me.

1686
00:51:31,160 --> 00:51:32,120
(Quest complete)
We'll all come find you.

1687
00:51:32,120 --> 00:51:33,200
(Bride missing edition)
Okay, I really need to go now.

1688
00:51:33,200 --> 00:51:33,920
Don't lose the ring.

1689
00:51:33,920 --> 00:51:35,000
They'll come find you for it.

1690
00:51:35,880 --> 00:51:36,800
They'll come find me for it?

1691
00:51:38,040 --> 00:51:39,560
Just don't lose it then.

1692
00:51:39,980 --> 00:51:40,480
(Fearless)

1693
00:51:40,480 --> 00:51:41,640
The bride will come find you for it.

1694
00:51:42,840 --> 00:51:44,040
Is the ring okay to keep?

1695
00:51:44,040 --> 00:51:44,400
Take it.

1696
00:51:44,400 --> 00:51:45,600
(Still a little scared)
The bride will come to you for it.

1697
00:51:45,600 --> 00:51:46,160
Just take it.

1698
00:51:46,520 --> 00:51:47,080
Terrifying.

1699
00:51:48,000 --> 00:51:49,040
Please don't come find me.

1700
00:51:49,040 --> 00:51:49,880
(Scared)

1701
00:51:49,880 --> 00:51:50,840
Bold of you.

1702
00:51:51,160 --> 00:51:52,480
Very bold.

1703
00:51:53,840 --> 00:51:54,480
Hold on.

1704
00:51:54,480 --> 00:51:55,760
Today is the 25th, right?

1705
00:51:55,760 --> 00:51:57,160
1996,

1706
00:51:57,160 --> 00:51:58,160
March 25th.

1707
00:51:58,160 --> 00:51:58,440
Right.

1708
00:51:58,440 --> 00:51:59,240
So we just

1709
00:51:59,240 --> 00:52:00,200
